    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="you-tides-verso.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <!-- This page consists of four different documents pasted together, none relating to the other -->
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <date when="1871-09-10">September 10, 1871<!--<ptr target="wwh.00026_n1"/>--></date>
                    <name type="place">New <gap reason="cut away" unit="word" quantity="1"/></name>
                </dateline>
                <salute>My <gap reason="cut away" unit="word" quantity="1"/> Walt</salute>
            </opener>
            <p> Have you seen the Springfield Repub <gap reason="cut away"/> 8th inst, with a 2 col. art on <gap
                    reason="cut away"/> Whitman? He does not <gap reason="cut away"/> know of a collected edition
                <gap reason="cut away"/> your works, and it appears
                    <gap reason="cut away"/> remarks as though it might <gap reason="cut away"/> while to
                send him a copy. If <gap reason="cut away"/> not the "Republican", I can <gap reason="cut away"/> to you. I send you a <gap
                    reason="cut away"/> &amp; wishes you might not <gap reason="cut away"/></p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Yours</salute>
                <signed><hi rend="underline">Hinton</hi></signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="you-tides-recto.jpg" type="verso"/>
            <!-- Whitman wrote poetry on this page, unrelated to letters -->
        </body>
    </text>
